Description: Resistive economy is a school and a strategy to achieve the minimum vulnerability and optimal point on the circumstances that independent variables such as economic sanctions and global restrictions, rule on economy. Therefore, due to develop the theme, scientific aspects and features of this economy, this journal has been set up to convey the ideological foundations of the resistive economy to literature of global economy. The Open Access Journal of Resistive Economics is a peer-reviewed open access journal that publishes original research articles, review articles, as well as case reports in a wide range of subjects in Economics, however articles published in the journal may appear in multiple subjects (Economy under Sanctions, Green Economics, Entrepreneurship, Military Economics and Management, Oil and Gas Economics and Management).
